Description: Small axe head made of grey basalt, roughly rectangular shape tapered towards the butt end, slightly convex at the blade end. The blade shows heavy traces of wear. The surface is well smoothed toward the blade end and roughly pitted towards the butt end.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.21 (south section), level 2-3
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 135)
